  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the performance of our zero-shot NER approach, we used two datasets: (1) the NCBI Disease Dataset, which contains annotations for 1382 unique disease names and concepts 68, (2) the Stanford MOUD NER Dataset, which contains annotations for 450 clinical entities and concepts.",
    "2) a target entity.",
    "Initially, our CLEAR implementation applies an NER model to the clinical notes to extract a dataset of relevant entities.",
    "These entities are then filtered using word embeddings and cosine similarity to ensure relevance to the target entity.",
    "Next, additional entities related to the target entity are identified using ontologies and LLMs."
